1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:03,216
GORDON: Previously on Gotham...

2
00:00:03,240 --> 00:00:04,389
<i>SOFIA: Harvey is weak,</i>

3
00:00:04,480 --> 00:00:07,393
<i>and how many more cops need to die
because of his incompetence?</i>

4
00:00:07,520 --> 00:00:10,353
As of this moment, I'm assuming
the Captaincy of Gotham Central.

5
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:12,033
Nothing in Gotham is free.

6
00:00:12,120 --> 00:00:14,760
You wanted a gangster to help you
get rid of Penguin.

7
00:00:14,840 --> 00:00:16,877
This is what that help looks like.

8
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:20,840
The whole town has gone
hog wild for the Pyg. (SNORTS)

9
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:24,318
<i>GORDON: Turns out the Pygk real name
is Lazlo Valentine.</i>

10
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:26,274
<i>And he just escaped.</i>

11
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:28,641
LEE: I haven't been looking
for a cure for your brain, Ed.

12
00:00:28,720 --> 00:00:30,056
Because I was afraid
that if I told you the truth,

13
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:31,991
<i>you would go back to being
who you were before.</i>

14
00:00:32,080 --> 00:00:34,071
<i>And I like who you've become.</i>

15
00:00:34,360 --> 00:00:36,033
<i>BRUCE: I'm not the hero Gotham needs.</i>

16
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,237
- I took the dark path.
- ALFRED: Yes, you did.

17
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:41,199
<i>And it's gonna be a long,
bumpy journey back.</i>

18
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:43,238
- What...
- Hello, Victor.

19
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:45,630
- Where's the boy?
- SOFIA: Alive, for now.

20
00:00:45,960 --> 00:00:47,553
<i>If Oswald wants to keep it that way,</i>

21
00:00:47,640 --> 00:00:49,677
<i>he will meet me under
the Crown Point Bridge...</i>

22
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:56,799
You wanted a war, you've got one!

23
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:02,837
We will wait for Mr. Cobblepot
to send instructions.

24
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:04,075
Åhh!

25
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:06,555
(ALL GRUNTING)

26
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:17,720
Hello.

27
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:25,273
Where is Penguin, little man?

28
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:58,398
This is Gordon.
I need forensics in West End Alley.

29
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:02,716
A black-market doc. Pyg was here.

30
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,678
Looks like he got a new face.

31
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,957
(CHOKING)

32
00:02:23,160 --> 00:02:24,160
(MR. PENN SCREAMING)

33
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:30,231
So, Penguin's out building
support amongst the gangs.

34
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:33,393
Pretty soon every criminal in Gotham
is gonna be hunting us.

35
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:36,395
He's out building support
because we made him look weak.

36
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:39,838
We kill him, and all the gangs
will support me.

37
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:42,954
- I'm still a Falcone.
- Yeah, you mentioned that.

38
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:44,993
- About a billion times.
- (DOOR OPENS)

39
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:53,399
(EXHALES) He doesn't know
where Penguin is.

40
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:56,640
(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

41
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,957
(SIGHS) What?

42
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,435
I'II be right there.

43
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:07,790
Is that about Penguin?

44
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,560
No.

45
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,030
Harper.

46
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:20,919
We were an hour outside of Gotham
when I got waylaid by Victor Zsasz.

47
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,277
He took Sofia. Gave me this.
Iwoke up in Virginia.

48
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:26,271
Damn it. I had a deal with Penguin.

49
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:28,176
There's more.
We're getting word Penguin had some

50
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,635
meeting under the Crown Point Bridge
late last night.

51
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:34,315
Gunfire. A car blown up.
Sofia Falcone was there.

52
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:36,477
AII right, we have
to find Penguin. Harper?

53
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,870
- I'm good, Cap.
- Put out a citywide BOLO.

54
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,871
- L'll find Sofia.
- HARPER: What about the Pyg?

55
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:44,590
- I heard he escaped from Arkham.
- Tracked him to a black market surgeon.

56
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:47,593
He's already got a new
face. Lazlo Valentine is gone.

57
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:50,069
- But if we don't find him...
- Focus on the bigger problem.

58
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,759
We've got a war to stop, people.

59
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:04,154
So, you're gonna tell us
why we're at your dad's house?

60
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,240
Why do you think?

61
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:17,880
Sofia.

62
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:23,389
You look tired.

63
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:27,189
Ms. Kean, it's good to see you again.

64
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:31,199
Likewise. So this is weird.

65
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:35,035
Why are you here, Father?

66
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:38,396
What did I tell you when you
asked to return to Gotham?

67
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,872
- I know...
- (LOUDLY) What did I tell you?

68
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:44,873
- That I wasn't ready.
- Exactly.

69
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,271
And you came back anyway.

70
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:51,796
Perhaps I should've acted then.
But I was indulgent.

71
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:55,760
Curious.
Who is this daughter I raised?

72
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:59,518
Father, Penguin is weak.

73
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,314
If you help me, <i>we</i> can end this.

74
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,357
I don't want Gotham.

75
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:05,397
I don't believe that.
You love this city.

76
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:07,915
I used to, yes.

77
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,915
But I'm dying, Sofia.

78
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:16,189
Someone else can have Gotham.
What I care about now is my family.

79
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:21,036
And I'm your family. And I want this.
I deserve this. Gotham belongs to me.

80
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:27,190
Your actions
have disgraced our family.

81
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,912
Tell me how sleeping with Jim Gordon,

82
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,038
the man who killed your brother,
helped reclaim Gotham.

83
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,320
I'm sorry, what?

84
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,989
I have done many things
Iwill have to answer for.

85
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:40,516
But I always knew
the meaning of honor.

86
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,118
You have proven that you do not.

87
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:49,360
Children... (CHUCKLES)

88
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:53,792
- They can be such disappointments.
- (SELINA GASPS)

89
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:01,076
I kill him, and this is over. Please.

90
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:03,717
You know why I came
when Penguin called?

91
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:06,158
It's because you were going to lose.

92
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:09,471
If you were anyone but my daughter.

93
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:12,033
You'd be dead right now.

94
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:29,993
Oh. Morning.

95
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,110
In there.

96
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,200
ALFRED: Dear, oh, dear.

97
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:40,277
Oh. Good morning, Officer.
My name is Alfred Pennyworth.

98
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:43,274
Neighbors called in
a noise complaint.

99
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:45,398
- He's all yours.
- Thank you.

100
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:49,720
Right.

101
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,355
(SCOFFS)

102
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:02,910
(ALL GASPING)

103
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,150
- Good morning, Master Bruce.
- WOMAN: Oh, my God!

104
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:07,390
Ido believe the party
is well and truly over.

105
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:11,070
Morning, miss. Good morning, miss.

106
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,480
GCPD.

107
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,991
- I'm looking...
- For my daughter.

108
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:25,395
You can stop. She's with me.

109
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,160
GORDON: Carmine.

110
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,359
I didn't expect to see you.

111
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,271
I imagine not.
I arrived this morning.

112
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:36,151
- You heard Sofia is in danger.
- Was in danger.

113
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:37,794
I made a deal with Cobblepot.

114
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:41,360
I take her out of Gotham today
and she lives.

115
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,957
I made the same deal,
he didn't keep it.

116
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:45,760
He will with me.

117
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,879
I'm glad I never killed you.

118
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:56,480
Thanks.

119
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:59,678
Don't thank me. Killing you
would have been a kindness.

120
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,876
You have no idea what you've brought
to your city.

121
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:07,195
I imagine when you find out
the truth, it will destroy you.

122
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,120
That's a comfort.

123
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:21,316
Another day. Another man
sending me out of Gotham.

124
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,198
We're both just trying
to keep you alive.

125
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,040
Tell yourself that.

126
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,759
But what I know is that neither
of you believed in me.

127
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:32,709
Could have been s0 different.

128
00:08:41,680 --> 00:08:43,318
Goodbye, James Gordon.

129
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:55,111
I doubt we'II see each other again.

130
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,752
The sun never shines here.

131
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,435
Everything I did, I did for your love.

132
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,074
That doesn't matter, does it?

133
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:15,749
What matters is that after
everything you've done,

134
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,150
I still consider you my daughter.

135
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:21,434
That's enough.

136
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:28,351
Mother planted those roses,
she loved them.

137
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:32,478
I wanna take one with me.

138
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:00,760
Get down!

139
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:19,395
(GASPS)

140
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,029
(INAUDIBLE)

141
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:48,710
<i>Gotham is still reeling
from the violent death</i>

142
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:51,076
<i>of Carmine Falcone three days ago.</i>

143
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:54,551
<i>Falcone ruled the Gotham underworld
for nearly 30 years.</i>

144
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:57,670
No arrests have been made
and a strange quiet...

145
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,518
Pleasant night, Master Bruce?

146
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:02,991
There's a mess in the Rolls.
You'll need a bucket.

147
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:08,193
MALE <i>NEWSCASTER: which many have
atlributed to the Pax Penguina.</i>

148
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:10,715
<i>Indeed, the Don 's claim
to the throne of Gotham...</i>

149
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:12,199
He shouldn't have come back.

150
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:15,079
<i>More recent years
by a new breed of criminal...</i>

151
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:17,436
<i>Leaving</i> some <i>to ask, does Gotham...</i>

152
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:18,749
Yes, Victor?

153
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:22,595
You would've told me, right?
If you were gonna ice the old man.

154
00:11:22,680 --> 00:11:26,230
(SCOFFS) Obviously!
Victor, I did not kill Don Falcone.

155
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:28,152
Well, everyone on the street
thinks you did.

156
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:31,835
So let 'em.
My hands are clean. You have my word.

157
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:34,216
MALE NEWSCASTER:
With Don Falcone's passing,

158
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:37,312
<i>it is unknown how or indeed when
the void of power</i>

159
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:40,438
<i>at the center of the city's
Underworld will be filled.</i>

160
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:46,072
(CHOIR SINGING)

161
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,109
GORDON: Sofia.

162
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:15,119
- I came to the hospital.
- I told them not to admit you.

163
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:20,070
- I am truly sorry about your father.
- You know it was Penguin.

164
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:23,199
And if I had evidence supporting
that, I'd arrest him.

165
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:27,035
He is over there, waiting to see
my face and gloat.

166
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:31,395
He is a liar.
And a murderer many times over.

167
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:34,153
But you need evidence.

168
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:38,953
I have to bury my father.

169
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:42,160
Excuse us.

170
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:49,280
(GASPS)

171
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,600
Victor!

172
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:50,600
- (SIGHS) Harvey.
- Jim.

173
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:52,555
Your leave is almost up.

174
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:56,519
- Be good to have you back.
- We'II see.

175
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:59,440
S0 why haven't you arrested
the little weasel?

176
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:04,473
Penguin still owns the judges.

177
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:07,429
If I arrest him,
and it's not rock solid, he'll walk.

178
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:10,034
So him whacking Falcone
and you sitting on your hands,

179
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:12,232
what good does that do?

180
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:22,436
It was Sofia who paid off the Mayor
to make me Captain.

181
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,000
I didn't ask her to.

182
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:26,510
Well, well.

183
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:29,399
She's been pressing me
to move on Penguin. Even before this.

184
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:31,240
I told you, didn't I?

185
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:33,874
That bill would come due.

186
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,197
I can't allow her to turn the GCPD
into her own private army.

187
00:14:39,280 --> 00:14:41,794
We've come too far.
This has to be by the book.

188
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:44,759
Then forget Falcone.

189
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,150
Penguin's too smart
to get nailed for that anyway.

190
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:50,715
What do you mean?

191
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:53,470
Get him to do something
you can really bust him for.

192
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:56,633
And then yank his ass off the street
once and for all.

193
00:14:57,760 --> 00:15:00,274
- You're saying start a war.
- I'm saying get him to start one.

194
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:01,919
You know he's gonna come for her.

195
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:04,432
I don't give a tinker's damn
about Sofia.

196
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:06,096
Way I see it,
everything that's happened.

197
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:08,236
Down to Don Falcone
lying in that box,

198
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:11,438
comes from you deciding months ago
to go after Penguin.

199
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:14,155
This is all on you.

200
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:18,393
S0 finish what you started.

201
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:32,034
PENGUIN: Goodbye, old friend.

202
00:15:34,520 --> 00:15:36,875
I will not forget
all that you taught me.

203
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:48,758
I had great respect for your father.

204
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:52,000
But once he's in the ground,
you are...

205
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:53,872
- Excuse me.
- (BREATHES HEAVILY)

206
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,270
Not here.

207
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:09,433
What're you doing, Jim?

208
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:10,919
Finishing what I started.

209
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:20,233
(INDISTINCT CHATFERING)

210
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:34,520
<i>Testing, testing, one, two, three.
James Gordon.</i>

211
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:37,109
<i>James Gordon.</i>

212
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,199
GORDON: What do you want, Oswald?

213
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:44,716
<i>You know what I want. Where is she?</i>

214
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,600
No.

215
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:51,190
<i>You're seriously going
to go to war for her?</i>

216
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,879
I'm upholding the law.

217
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:57,038
No one gets to decide
who lives or dies in Gotham.

218
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:02,914
<i>Can you not see, Jim?
She's manipulated you and lied...</i>

219
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:04,633
The law is the law.

220
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:09,195
Now either get over it
or face the consequences.

221
00:17:10,120 --> 00:17:11,315
(MICROPHONE FEEDBACK)

222
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:14,714
Let's try it this way.

223
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:21,714
Sofia Falcone is in this building,
whoever brings her to me

224
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:23,791
will be richly rewarded.

225
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:25,871
I'm going to count to five.

226
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:27,216
Count as much as you want, twerp.

227
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:29,595
Yeah, we don't work for you.

228
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:37,518
This man is asking you to risk
your lives to protect a gangster!

229
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:41,634
I am offering you money. Huh?

230
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:46,351
And bonus, no one gets killed. (LAUGHS)

231
00:17:46,520 --> 00:17:48,716
Hey, Captain, can we?

232
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:50,195
Sure.

233
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:52,959
Get off me.

234
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:57,477
Blood will run, Jim.
Mark my words! Blood will run!

235
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:59,039
It will be on your hands!

236
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:00,710
(PENGUIN YELLING)

237
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,912
(OFFICERS JEERING)

238
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:13,431
From the first day
I put on the badge,

239
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:17,470
I was told things could never change.

240
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:22,639
Gotham was corrupt. GCPD was corrupt.

241
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:26,510
Criminals and lowlifes ran things.

242
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:31,438
You just showed me different.

243
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:35,239
Penguin will be coming.

244
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,755
It's time we showed Gotham
